parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of brake lines can cause the loss of brake fluid, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
brake fluid leaking from under the vehicle
soft or spongy brake pedal
pulsating brake pedal
loss of braking power
ABS warning lights illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: ABS warning lights illuminated
pulsating brake pedal
loss of braking power
vehicle takes longer to stop
feeling of the brakes "grabbing" or "pulsing".

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Parking brake does not hold the vehicle in place
parking brake warning lights illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the loss of power steering and power brakes, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
sometimes while driving at high speeds
and may restart after a few minutes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust manifold bolts can cause the release of carbon monoxide, affecting the oxygen sensor and catalytic converter, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The exhaust manifold bolts break
causing a loud rattling noise
and the check engine light may illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
sometimes while driving at high speeds
and may restart after a few minutes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the loss of steering control, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels heavy or difficult to turn
the power steering pump fails
the steering wheel locks up
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel has a clunking or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intermediate steering shaft can cause the loss of steering control, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel has a clunking or grinding noise
the steering wheel feels loose or unstable
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel has a knocking sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the loss of steering control, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels off-center
the steering column collapses
the airbag does not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the loss of clutch function, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the vehicle can cause the loss of power steering and brakes, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls suddenly
the vehicle loses power steering and brakes
the vehicle is unable to start again.
